    <text id="B0202T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell's letter to Waldo concerns invoices for clothing.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/>Head <abbr expan="Quarters">Qrs</abbr>. 9<hi rend="super">t</hi>
                    Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">R. Waldo<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A.
                        Comr</abbr><lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-12-17"><abbr expan="December">Dec</abbr> 17. <abbr expan="1868">68</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>In reply to your letter of 14 inst. this day received, you are respectfully
                    informed that the <unclear>Gt</unclear> &amp; <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>: Coats (15
                    each) Invoiced to you by <abbr expan="Major">Maj</abbr> White are the same as
                    these sent by <abbr expan="Major">Maj.</abbr> Brown &amp; that your receipt
                    has been cancelled and the Invoices returned to <abbr expan="Major">Maj.</abbr>
                    White, they having already been receipted for by me, <abbr expan="though">tho'</abbr>
                    <unclear>incorrectly</unclear> described.</p>

                <p>All the clothing you are expected to <abbr expan="account">acct</abbr> for is
                    that enumerated in my letters of 14<hi rend="super">t</hi> &amp; 15<hi
                        rend="super">t</hi> inst.</p>

                <p>As certificates that this has been properly <abbr expan="accounted">acct</abbr>
                    of &amp; an examination of <abbr expan="accounts">accts</abbr> has to be
                    made before final payment, it is important that all <unclear>
                        <abbr expan="assessments?">asss</abbr>
                    </unclear> should be sent in as early as 25<hi rend="super">t</hi> as mentioned
                    in my previous letter.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S. A.
                            Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
